  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT178-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">kaṭinakar pukka tōḻi talaimakaṉ puṇarcci vitumpal kaṇṭu muṉṉark kaḷavukkālattoḻukalāṟ(C1: kaḷavu kaṟṟoḻukal; C5: kaḷavu kantoḻukal) āṟṟāmai niṉaintu aḻintu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante, who had entered the marriage house, speaking, desolate when thinking of [his] lack of strength formerly in the time of secrecy, upon seeing HIS yearning for union.</p>
          </div>


        <div xml:id="KT178">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                ayirai paranta vantaṇ paḻaṉat</l>
<l>                tēnteḻiṉ malara tūmpuṭait tiraḷkā</l>
<l>                lāmpal kuṟunar nīrvēṭ ṭāṅkiva</l>
<l>                ḷiṭaimulaik kiṭantu naṭuṅka lāṉīr</l>
<l>                toḻutukāṇ piṟaiyiṟ ṟōṉṟi yānumak</l>
<l>                kariya mākiya kālaip</l>
<l>                periya nōṉṟaṉir nōkō yāṉē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
           <l>You have become all a-quiver, laid down between her breasts,</l>
           <l rend="indent">like people craving water while plucking waterlilies</l>
           <l rend="indent">with tubular, round stems [and] blossoms<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">malara</term>: it is unclear what is to be achieved by the pronominal noun here. Perhaps it is rather to be analysed as an infinitive: "so that they flower eminent in grace"?</note> of exceeding grace</l>
           <l rend="indent">in the nice cool pond where Ayirai fish have spread.<note place="foot">Cām.'s gloss, according to which <term xml:lang="ta">Ayirai</term> fish feed on waterlilies, would explain their presence in the poem, but it is not supported by the text in any way. Moreover it is unclear whether <term xml:lang="ta">paranta</term> is to be connected with <term xml:lang="ta">paḻaṉam</term> or with <term xml:lang="ta">āmpal</term>, in other words, whether it is intended to establish a relationship between the fish and the lilies or only between the fish and the pond.</note></l>
           <l rend="indent">At that time when we were difficult for you [to obtain],</l>
           <l rend="indent">appearing [as we did] like the crescent moon, seen [and]</l>
           <l rend="indent4">worshipped,</l>
           <l>you suffered greatly. Ah, I ache.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
